DataElement.preferredName: Demographics Address Census Tract  1970/80/90 Number Text
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The numbers that describe the Census Tract or Block Numbering Area for a location as defined by boundaries identified in 1970, 1980, or 1990.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The set of Census Bureau census tract definitions (boundaries) that were used to code the census tract in Census Tract 1970/80/90 [110] for a specific record.

Property.preferredDefinition: The location at which an organization or person can be reached. ValueDomain.preferredName: Census Tract/Block Numbering Area 1970/80/90 Number Text
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: The number between 001000 and 949999 that represents the Census Tract or a number between 950100 and 998999 that represents the Block Numbering Area for a location.  These boundaries are defined for the years 1970, 1980, or 1990.
